Before finalizing, I should inspect whether there is any existing formatting or nearby content around `B2`, then write a robust formula. Because `A1` may contain extra text beyond the key (as seen with `8CPARK /...`), I should match on substring presence, case-insensitively if possible. A nested `IF(ISNUMBER(SEARCH(...)))` formula is LibreOffice-compatible and avoids issues with unsupported dynamic functions. I’ll save to the output directory, recalculate, and verify that `B2` evaluates to `6` for the current `A1`.
